Let's look at the argument in more detail:---ÒIn all irreducibly complex systems in which the cause of the system is known by experience or observation, intelligent design or engineering played a role [in] the origin of the system.Ó Now remember that complexity refers to our absence to understand how to explain something, and that the statement basically states that "when we do not understand something" and it is "irreducible" then it must be designed.
